<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Confident About Spain Joining Euro on Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 9 (Xinhua) -- French Minister of Finance and
Economy Dominique Strauss-Kahn today expressed his confidence that
Spain will be able to join the European single currency euro in
the first wave in January 1999.
</P>
<P>
"In regard to the performance of the Spanish economy in the
past several years, it seems to me that the process of convergence
predicted by the (Maastricht) treaty is perfectly fulfilled,
better than others," said Strauss-Kahn at a joint press
conference with his Spanish counterpart, Rodrigo de Rato.
</P>
<P>
He said that the will of the Spanish government to be one of
the original members of the monetary union is justified by the
"very concrete" economic performance of the country.
</P>
<P>
Rato said that there is "almost a unanimity" of agreement in
Spain to the country's joining the euro as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers agreed that the economic growth of their
countries is "accelerating" and that the economic situation will
be better in 1998 than this year for both countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
