<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Becomes Agent on Loans for Nuclear Power Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The National Development Bank
of China (NDBC) and the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
(ICBC) signed an agreement here today to let the latter act as
agent in handling foreign loans for the third phase construction
of the Qinshan Nuclear Power Station.
</P>
<P>
It is the 475th proxy project between the two banks. The NDBC
has few branches, and the majority of its business is done by
commercial banks as its agents.
</P>
<P>
The third phase of Qinshan is a state key project in the Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) period, with a capacity of 1.4 million
kw and a total investment of 2.88 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Canada, the United States and Japan, among others, have
provided the project with over two billion US dollars of export
credits, and foreign banks have offered 626 million US dollars of
commercial loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
