<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comoran President Takes over Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Comoran President Mohamed
Abdoulkarim Taki today took control of the government and said he
would form a new government of national union within three weeks,
after the situation on the island of Anjouan becomes normal.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Federal Republic of the Comoras has been troubled
by separatists on Anjouan Island -- one of three islands which
make up the nation -- for more than one month.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a Comoran army intervention last week in Anjouan
resulted in a fiasco and the death of more than 50 people,
including 40 Comoran government soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Taki announced earlier today the dissolution of the civil and
military government of the country, and said that he would be
personally in charge of the Interior Ministry, according to Agence
France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Taki said the Arab League, the United Nations and the
Organization of African Unity are all helping Comoros end the
separatism of Anjouan and establish a government of national union
with a national program.
</P>
<P>
"The events in Anjouan should be prevented from every happening
again," he said. "After the situation becomes normal, in Anjouan
in particular, I will establish a government of national
union... so that peace, fraternity and democracy will be
re-established," said Taki.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that the National Assembly of the country
would begin holding an extraordinary session today "in full
power." 
</P>
</TEXT>
