<HEADLINE> Spanish Marathon Team Wins Prince of Asturias Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Spain's national marathon team
was awarded the prestigious Prince of Asturias sports prize
Tuesday in Oviedok, Spain.
</P>
<P>
A prize jury including International Olympic Committee chairman
Juan Antonio Samaranch cited the team for its repeated successes in
the international arena.
</P>
<P>
The team composed of Martin Fiz, Abel Anton, Fabian Roncero
and Jose Mstar and Olympic gold medalist Fermin Cacho.
</P>
<P>
The sports prize is one of eight Prince of Asturias awards given
each year in fields also including science, literature, arts and
peacemaking.
</P>
<P>
American track star Carl Lewis was awarded last year's sports
prize. Previous winners include Algerian athlete Hassiba Boulmerka,
tennis star Martina Navratilova and Cuban high jumper Javier
Sotomayor. 
</P>
