<HEADLINE> Kanu May Leave Inter Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Olympic champion
Nwankwo Kanu said in Milan on Tuesday that he might be leaving
Inter Milan.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Nigerian hero, back in football less than a
year after heart surgery, found there is little or no room left
for him.
</P>
<P>
With Ronaldo guaranteed one of the two striking positions,
there are still several others in the attacking position.
</P>
<P>
Along with Kanu are Maurizio Ganz, Marco Branca, Ivan Zamorano,
Alvaro Recoba and Youri Djorkaeff. 
