<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mir Computer Repaired </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A Russian space official said
today the crew of the Mir space station has repaired the main
on-board computer which failed Monday.
</P>
<P>
The function of the gyroscopic devices, which keep the
station's solar panels in line with the sun to enable them to
generate power, was resumed. The devices failed Monday after the
computer failure.
</P>
<P>
The cosmonauts are expected to gradually restart the equipment,
which had been switched off, and examine and repair parts of the
system they depend on for life.
</P>
<P>
Accidents have frequently occurred on the Mir space station
which was established in 1986. It has lasted longer than its
expected five-year term, and a lack of funds has prevented Russia
from setting up new space stations.
</P>
<P>
About 1,450 failures have reportedly occurred on the Mir in the
past 11 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
