<HEADLINE> Cantona Turns down United Invitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Eric Cantona has written a
"pleasant" letter to his former club Manchester United, politely
turning down an invitation to a celebration dinner, a United
spokesman said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The French star, who quit United after deciding to retire at
the end of last season, had been invited back to Old Trafford
this weekend to celebrate the 1996-97 Championship victory.
</P>
<P>
But club secretary Ken Merrett said that the club had received
a letter from Cantona and his wife Isobel saying they were unable
to attend.
</P>
<P>
It was hoped that he could have taken a final bow before the
Premiership match against West Ham and then been guest of honour
on Sunday at a dinner for players and staff to mark the title win.
</P>
<P>
United hadn't received any reply from Cantona for weeks and
didn't know if he would be there or if he would snub the club
after a row over profits from merchandising sold in his name.
</P>
<P>
But Merrett said: "We have at last received a letter from Eric
and his wife. It was a very pleasent one.
</P>
<P>
"The tone was good, but he said he would be unable to
attend. He just said he was unavailable but that it had been a
kind invitation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
