<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Recover on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
recover on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index rebounded by another 27.95 points to close at
1919.88 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 476.07 million units, worth 839.2
million Singapore dollars (about 559.47 million U.S. dollars).
Advances led declines by 225 to 131, while 253 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac again was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 39.51 million units. It was followed by
the Asian Food &AMP; Property (AFP) which had 27.66 million shares
traded. Ber Group was next with 19.61 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Asean Fund led the gainers of the day as it rose 1.3
dollars to finish at 11.8 U.S. dollars. City Developments
warrant98 gained 1.1 dollars to end at 8.5 Singapore dollars,
while City Developments and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH)
Foreign each increased one dollar to close at 11.1 and 24.5
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, BMT 100 was the biggest loser as it declined
12 dollars to end at 88 dollars. Genting 200 fell 3.35 dollars to
close at 5.6 Singapore dollars. Cerebos, Malaya Banking and MAA
each lost 20 cents to finish at 5.85, 9.8, and 5.55 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
