<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Severs Ties with Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONROVIA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to Liberia
Xie Zhiheng today reproached the Liberian government for forging
official ties with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Xie accused the Liberian government of brazenly creating "two
Chinas," saying that the wrong move by Liberia has seriously
harmed China's sovereignty and constituted interference in China's
internal affairs and undermined the foundation of normal
diplomatic relations between China and Liberia.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government strongly protests at the
Liberian government and has decided to sever diplomatic ties with
Liberia as of today and the implementation of all agreements
between the two countries ceases with immediate effect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
