<HEADLINE> CPC Congress Deputies Selected Through Democratic Process (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Wang Jingxia, a 37-year old
woman from a textile mill in eastern Shandong Province, arrived in
Beijing by train today along with other delegates from her home
province to attend the upcoming congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Wang, a technician in the Jinan Chengtong Textile Co. Ltd, is
one of the 2,048 delegates to participate in the 15th CPC National
Congress, which is to open Friday.
</P>
<P>
Official sources noted that all delegates to the CPC congress
have been chosen through a democratic process: they were first
nominated by the Party's grassroots bodies; later subjected to a
comprehensive questioning by the higher authorities; and finally
elected at the local Party congresses.
</P>
<P>
"The CPC Central Committee has asked that democracy be brought
into full play within the Party regarding election of the
delegates, and we have practiced democracy throughout the whole
selection process," said Wang Keyu, head of the Organizational
Department of the Provincial CPC Committee of Shandong.
</P>
<P>
A Party official from Wang Jingxia's mill explained how Wang
became a delegate, pointing out that the higher Party
organizations did not name any candidates for the national Party
congress this year.
</P>
<P>
CPC members in his factory had been urged to elect whomever
they deemed qualified to be a delegate, he said, and the mill's
Party committee prepared a namelist of candidates for the
committee at the next higher level, based on the will of the
majority of the CPC members in the factory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Congress Delegates Selected Through Democratic Process (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wang Jingxia has taken first place honors in a series of
national workers' contests of technical skill. She has also been
named one of the ten outstanding workers in the country and a
national model worker. One of her tying-in operational methods has
been popularized throughout the industry.
</P>
<P>
"She is an excellent representative of us textile workers," said
her colleague Liu Yanrong.
</P>
<P>
The textile company nominated six candidates, including Wang,
to the Party committee of the city's textile bureau, and then the
bureau's committee passed on 40 candidates, including Wang and
candidates from other units, to the CPC city committee of
Jinan, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The city Party committee selected six people from over 140
candidates from all local units as the city's candidates, and
reported the list to the Shandong Provincial Party committee.
</P>
<P>
On June 13, the CPC provincial committee appointed 70 people to
be the members of the provincial delegation to join the Party
congress.
</P>
<P>
During the months of selection, 4.42 million CPC members from
241,000 grassroots Party branch committees took part, 93.9 percent
and 99.2 percent of the total in this east China province,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
"Party members have exercised the highest degree of democracy
this time and the election of candidates has had involved so many
party organizations and their members," said Wang Keyu.
</P>
<P>
According to the CPC Central Committee's Organizational
Department, more than half a million candidates emerged in the
first round of selections nationwide, and over 3.2 million Party
branches, 95 percent of the total, and some 50 million Party
members, over 85 percent of the total, recommended their own
candidates.
</P>
<P>
After Wang was made a delegate, she has spent her spare time
visiting and talking with her fellow workers and soliciting their
opinions about the job ahead.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very honored to be elected a delegate to the National
Party Congress and also feel a tremendous sense of
responsibility," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, she said, "as a representative of the 4.5 million CPC
members in Shandong province, I will express the will, proposals
and opinions of industrial workers in the factories, mines and
other indutrial enterprises." 
</P>
</TEXT>
