<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Volume of Eurotunnel Keeps Rising in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Channel Tunnel operator
Eurotunnel's recovery from last November's fire continued last
month as traffic on Le Shuttle trains rose 25 percent following a
29.5 percent rise in July.
</P>
<P>
Figures released today by the company showed that so far this
year, Le Shuttle has carried more than 1.34 million vehicles,
little changed from the same period last year when it carried 1.39
million, despite the reduced service due to the fire.
</P>
<P>
The company said that a new daily record was set on August 29
when it carried 10,986 vehicles in a single day. And the company's
cross-Channel market share is now more than 40 percent, compared
with last year's peak of 45 percent before the fire.
</P>
<P>
The number of passengers carried on Eurostar grew by 4.5
percent last month compared with July and was up 20 percent from a
year ago to a record 681,663.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Le shuttle's freight service has recaptured 67
percent of its previous market in only two months as the service
did not start again after the fire until June although freight
traffic is usually lower during August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
