<HEADLINE> Greek Inflation in August Rises Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The annual consumer price
inflation in Greece increased from 5.4 percent in July to 5.6
percent in August, the National Statistics Service (NSS) announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Electricity and petrol prices burdened the consumer price index
by 0.07 percent and 0.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The NSS expected the inflation rate to ease this month.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that there was
a slight deviation from this year's inflation target, but he
stressed that it was a temporary phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
In August last year, the country's consumer price inflation was
8.0 percent. 
</P>
