building demanding for manifestation of nearly four years of
benefits, including insurance.
</P>
<P>
The trouble is seen by observers as an event to mark the first
labor unrest in post-war Liberia and challenge the ability of the
Charles Taylor administration to seek a broad range of benefits
for workers.  
