<HEADLINE> East African Labor Management Body Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Eleven east African
nations have set up a sub-regional labor management team for
their countries, Pan African News Agency reported today from
Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
The team was formed under an agreement with the International
Labor Organization (ILO), and its task is to advise and give
guidance on employers' organizations, governments and workers in
these countries.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Deputy Foreign Minister Tekeda Alemu and ILO's
Deputy Director-general Mary Chinery signed the formal agreement
today in Addis Ababa establishing the east African
multi-disciplinary advisory team.
</P>
<P>
The team will offer advisory services in international labor
standards, help strengthen employers' and workers' organizations,
promote employment, labor relations and administration.
</P>
<P>
The team will be based in the Ethiopian capital, Addis Ababa,
and cover Comoros, Djibouti, Ethiopia, Eritrea, Kenya,
Madagascar, Mauritius, Seychelles, Somalia, Tanzania and Uganda.
</P>
