<HEADLINE> Iranian Revolution Guards Commander Replaced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Yehya Rahim Safavi today was
named as the new commander of Iran's Islamic Revolution's Guards
Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
State-run radio and television reported that Iran's Supreme
Leader Ali Khamenei issued a decree to replace Mohsen Rezaie with
Safavi, who had been deputy commander, as head of the IRGC.
</P>
<P>
Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani, Iran's former president and now
chairman of the State Expediency Council (SEC), has appointed
Rezaie as SEC secretary.
</P>
<P>
But the reports gave no reason for the removal of the former
IRGC commander.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, a well-informed source told Xinhua that Rezaie
was removed from the IRGC because he is against the liberal
faction including new President Mohammad Khatami and interfered in
the presidential election in May.
</P>
<P>
Some reports said that Rezaie carried out political activities
in the presidential elections in the interests of hardliner
Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri.
</P>
<P>
Before the announcement of the removal, unofficial reports said
that Rezaie had submitted his resignation to Khamenei in June and
that the latter had accepted the resignation.
</P>
<P>
But Rezaie denied any resignation move later.
</P>
<P>
The IRGC is an elite force in the Islamic Republic and
directly controlled by Khamenei. It has about 170,000 forces in
ground forces, naval forces and marines. 
