<HEADLINE> Mild Seven Outdoor Quest to Begin in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, Sichuan Province, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Mild
Seven Outdoor Quest, an adventure race, will start in Xichang,
Sichuan provine of China from Thursday to Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Mild Seven Outdoor Quest, a grueling challenge, will race
up to eight hours a day in pursuit of victory.
</P>
<P>
Events will include trail running, mountain biking, offroad
inline skating, river paddling, lake paddling, mountain bike
biathlon, and mountaineering. Each team includes at least one
woman.
</P>
<P>
Competitors will carry all their own food and water. If a
teammate is out by injury or broken will, the entire team will
be disqualified. Lowest overall time at the end of four days is
the winner. 
