<HEADLINE> Diners Club Opens Representative Office in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Diners Club International, a
subsidiary of Citibank, opened its first representative office in
China here today.
</P>
<P>
Located in the lobby of Bright China Chang'an Building, the
office will provide travel and entertainment-related services to
its cardmembers visiting and living in China, said Brian Clayton,
Citibank's North Asia Division Executive for Global Consumer
Banking.
</P>
<P>
Diners Club is comprised of more than 50 franchises around the
world serving over three million selected service establishments,
500 of which are in Beijing including hotels, stores and travel
agencies.
</P>
<P>
The card is accepted in more than 175 countries and regions,
and has seven million cardmembers worldwide, Clayton said.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has received an increasing number of overseas travelers
over the past few years, with the number coming to 2.18 million
last year.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing is the first important place in China for Diners Club
to drop anchor," said Clayton. "The establishment of the office
here shows our long-term confidence in China's financial and
service industries."
</P>
<P>
Citibank opened a full-service commercial banking branch in
Beijing in October 1995 -- the first US bank to do so.
</P>
<P>
John Beeman, chief representative of the Country Corporate
Office for Citibank China, said that the bank will continue to
invest in and develop its business in China and to take part in
the country's economic growth. 
</P>
