<HEADLINE> U.S. Funds Nepal's Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Agency for
International Development (USAID) has provided Nepal with about
895,000 U.S. dollars for accelerating its agricultural growth, the
official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This grant is part of a commitment by the USAID to contribute
some 29.8 million dollars over a period of six years to help Nepal
alleviate rural poverty through increasing sustainable production
and sales of forest and high-value agricultural products, the RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
Under the assistance agreement, the Nepali government and the
USAID are working to expand farmers' participation in producing
and marketing forest products and high-value agricultural products
such as fruits, vegetables, vegetable seeds, livestock and
livestock products, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Commercial sales of forest products and high-value agricultural
products in the USAID-funded areas nearly doubled over the past
year, rising from 466 million rupees (8.2 million dollars) to 886
million rupees (15.5 million dollars), the agency added.
</P>
<P>
The United States is among the Nepal Aid Group, which also
includes the Asian Development Bank and the World Bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
