<HEADLINE> 11 Killed in California Vehicle Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed
and four others were injured on Tuesday night in a collision
between a van filled with people and a truck in California.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on a scenic highway near the San Julian
Ranch, about 225 kilometers northwest of Los Angeles, at about
9:50 p.m. (0450 GMT Wednesday). Both vehicles were engulfed in
flames when rescue team arrived.
</P>
<P>
Six bodies were found inside the charred wreckage of the van,
two others were found on the road, and three bodies were found
which authorities believe came from the truck, the Associated
Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
When the accident occurred, that particular section of highway
was undergoing repairs and construction. Concrete barriers were
located near the crash site. 
</P>
