<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Help Indonesia in Cloud Seeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today pledged
to extend technical assistance to Indonesia including providing
the aircraft to carry out cloud seeding to improve the haze
condition caused by forest fires in that country.
</P>
<P>
Science, Technology and Environment Minister Law Hieng Ding
said here today he had directed the Meteorological Services
Department to provide the expertise and negotiate with the Pan
Malaysian Air Transport to get a suitable aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government was prepared to carry out cloud
seeding from the Riau archipelago and its Environment Minister
Sarwono Kusumaatmadja has written to him two days ago seeking
Malaysia's help to carry out the cloud seeding, Law Hieng Ding was
quoted by the Malaysian national news agency Bernama as saying.
</P>
<P>
Law said several air transport companies would be asked to
provide a suitable plane as the aircraft of the Pan Malaysian Air
Transport would be involved in air surveillance for a private
company next week.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft would also be deployed for cloud seeding in Kedah,
northern Malaysia, next month, he said.
</P>
<P>
The haze, which, according to the Indonesian minister in his
letter to Law, was caused by five major agricultural companies
which were found to be involved in the burning of forests covering
8,000 hectares in Kalimantan, Sumatra and Riau, has blanketed the
region since May and Malaysia has been enveloped by the haze since
mid July.
</P>
<P>
Law is scheduled to attend the ASEAN Environment Ministers'
Meeting in Jakarta next week where according to him the haze
situation and ways to overcome it would take center stage.
</P>
</TEXT>
