<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Loan to Manila Air Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has approved a 150,000 U.S. dollar loan to help fund a Metro
Manila Air Quality Improvement Project, the Philippine Environment
and Natural Resources Department said today.
</P>
<P>
As an initiative of the Philippine government, the project aims
to examine and determine the elements of an urban air quality
management strategy developed earlier by an inter-agency group
that includes experts from non-government and international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The ADB grant will fund the review of proposals for introducing
a motor vehicle inspection system, assessing the governance and
human resources issues associated with air quality and
environmental management, and enforcement of air quality
regulations.
</P>
<P>
The project will also include monitoring of public health,
assessment of public awareness needs, traffic engineering and road
rehabilitation requirements, and undertake an economic analysis of
various strategies in mitigating air quality deterioration.
</P>
<P>
Studies show that air quality in Metro Manila is deteriorating
rapidly as the country's economy surges ahead, the department
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
