<HEADLINE> Myanmar's First Private Gem Fair Opens in Yangon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's first private gem
fair -- Yangon Gem '97 Exhibition sponsored by local private
companies opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The five-day gem fair was organized by the TTF (Yangon) Co.
Ltd. with the support of the Myanmar Ministry of Hotels and
Tourism.
</P>
<P>
Jewelry and artifacts manufactured by the private sector are
displayed at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Local private entrepreneurs have been allowed to operate gem
and jade mining, and transport and sell their finished gemstones
and manufactured jewelry at home or abroad under the new Myanmar
Gemstone Law promulgated in September 1995.
</P>
<P>
Since 1964, state-sponsored gem exhibitions have been held
annually. Turnover at the 34th exhibition in March was over 250
million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
