<HEADLINE> International Trade Fair Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A six-day consumer
international trade fair opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Nepal, Pakistan, Bangladesh, India and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea are participating in the fair, said the
organizer Everest Exhibitions Private Limited of Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the fair, Nepali Industry Minister Keshav Badal
urged Nepali business community to raise productivity by utilizing
indigenous raw materials and introduce the domestic products into
the international market.
</P>
<P>
On display at the fair are a rich variety of items, including
clothing, household products, food stuff, cosmetic and beauty
products, jewelry, art and crafts, gifts and novelties, footwear,
electrical appliances, beverages and furniture.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair, which opened weeks away from the Dashain
festival, the biggest traditional festival in Nepal, attracted a
large number of shoppers.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, entertainment programs like fashion show, pop
music contest, bicycle rally, kite flying contest, food festival,
coca cola and beer drinking contest and movie shows will also be
presented.  
