<HEADLINE> Chinese People Wish Party Congress Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- People around China have
written to the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) wishing success to the upcoming 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
The nearly 1,000 letters all expressed the hope that the
congress will accelerate the reform and opening-up pace of China,
and become a new milestone in the history of the CPC and China's
socialist modernization, according to an official of the General
Office of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
A bank employee in Hubei Province said in his letter that
China's socialist construction has made remarkable achievements
since the 14th National Congress five years ago, and China has
been the strongest, its people the most prosperous, and its
international status the highest in the country's history.
</P>
<P>
"It is of great significance and has far-reaching influence
for the Party to convene the 15th National Congress at this
historic movent to summarize the successful experience since China
adopted the reform and opening-up policy and explain the principles
and policies in the near future," the man wrote.
</P>
<P>
Many people said in their letters that the leadership of the
CPC is the fundamental guarantee for national prosperity.
</P>
<P>
One letter from Xi'an said China's experience since the Third
Plenary Session of the 11th CPC Central Committee in 1978 has
proved that the CPC has the ability to administer a country well,
and he hoped the 15th CPC National Congress will become a great
force for reform and opening-up.  
</P>
</TEXT>
