<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Career over the Past Five Years (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A Xinhua special report today
records the glorious achievements of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) from its 14th National Congress in October 1992 to the
coming 15th Congress, which is scheduled to open on September 12.
</P>
<P>
In the autumn five years ago, it says, the 14th CPC National
Congress adopted Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics as its guiding principle, and declared to
the whole world that the goal of China's economic reform is to
establish a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the third-generation of central
leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core have held Deng's theory
high, and guided the whole nation to seize opportunities and
accelerate development. Remarkable accomplishments have since been
made in a broad range of fields.
</P>
<P>
"Looking back to reform and opening-up and modernization over
the past five years," the report says, "we have concluded that the
Party Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core is a
mature, strong, and promising leadership, which has won the
support and trust of the whole Party, the whole army and people of
all ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, members of the third generation of
the collective Party leadership have made inspections and
investigations around the country to bring the ties between the
Party and the masses closer, and to make the Party's policies more
in line with the people's basic interests.
</P>
<P>
"They have derived wisdom and sustenance from the people, while
people have seen the future and hope because of them," the report
says.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture has been one issue that most deeply concerns
General Secretary Jiang Zemin and other central leaders.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Jiang was talking with farmers on matters
ranging from how to lessen their workloads and boost their income,
to how to fortify the status of agriculture, Premier Li Peng was
visiting people in flood-stricken areas and offering the support
and concern of the Party and the government. Meanwhile,
Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji was working to formulate policies to
protect the production of grain and cotton.
</P>
<P>
During the five years, the CPC Central Committee has drafted
several important policies concerning agriculture, which laid the
foundation for the sustained, stable and healthy development of
the sector.
</P>
<P>
With the deepening of reform and opening-up, state-owned
enterprises are facing a grave challenge. How to revitalize
state-owned enterprises, a pillar of the national economy, has
become an issue of greatest importance to the CPC Central
Committee, says the report.
</P>
<P>
During the five years, Jiang Zemin has visited state-owned
enterprises in a number of provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions, and made important speeches on reform of
state-owned enterprises to boost morale.
</P>
<P>
His speeches set the guidelines for further revitalization of
the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
