<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Career over the Past Five Years  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wherever they went, the leaders of CPC Central Committee
visited local families, chatting with them and asking for their
opinions. They did their utmost to solve the difficulties of the
people.
</P>
<P>
When President Jiang came to Baise in south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region in 1990, he was greatly distressed by the
sight of shanty houses and the impoverished local residents. Six
years later, when he paid the second visit, the local people, who
now lived new houses, surrounded him to say thank you.
</P>
<P>
Facing tens of millions of people who are still in need,
Chinese leaders frequently visited backward regions to send their
warm regards. Premier Li Peng, for instance, went to Yan'an of
Shaanxi Province in northwest China, and Xingguo County of east
China's Jiangxi Province respectively during the spring festivals
of 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
"During my trips to southwest and northwest China, I found that
some families even have difficulty in obtaining salt and drinkable
water," Jiang said with feelings.
</P>
<P>
"No matter how hard the campaign to wipe out poverty is, we
will go all out to win it," Jiang declared on behalf of the CPC
Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, in his surveys across the country,
repeatedly called on people's congresses at all levels to adhere
to the central task of economic development, while at the same
time emphasizing the construction of a socialist democracy and
legal system.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, agreed with
Qiao that building socialist democracy serves an indispensable
role in carrying out economic construction in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that Jiang had made over 40 inspections trips
in various places in the country. Another six members of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee made more than 150 surveys in all. Pragmatic and
enthusiastic as their working styles are, they have won hearty
support and trust from people nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The year 1992, marked by late leader Deng Xiaoping's important
remarks in his trip to southern China and the convocation of the 14th
CPC National Congress, unveiled a new era for the advance of the
cause of socialism in China.
</P>
<P>
During the past five years, the seven plena convened by the
Party Central Committee have basically mapped out the strategy
that will lead China into the next century. The strategy, in turn,
is testimony to the capability of the third generation leadship to
handle the country's reforms and opening up.
</P>
<P>
The Party Central Committee has deemed the coming 15 years to
be a crucial period when a comparatively sound socialist market
economy will be established. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
