<HEADLINE> China Puts on New Look in World: Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China has experienced
world-shaking changes in the past years and is now standing in
the world with a totally new look, Secretary-general of the
Angola-China Friendship Association Gentil Viana has said.
</P>
<P>
Viana, a witness of China's changes, made the remarks in a
special interview here recently with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"Things have completely changed," said Viana. It is "beyond
belief" that since China adopted the policy of reforms and
opening to the outside world in the 1980s, China has registered
such rapid changes both in the rural and urban areas, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Viana went to China with his parents when he was a child,
lived and studied there. Two decades later he returned as a
grown-up and visited China twice a year since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the changes China has undergone, he could not
help pouring out words in broken Chinese, saying that in
present-day China, modern buildings have mushroomed; wide roads
are seen here and there; and goods abound in the markets.
</P>
<P>
"Gone are the days when coupons on food and a lot of daily
necessities were issued in China," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Viana spoke highly of Deng Xiaoping, the late Chinese leader
and general architect of China's reforms. He attributed China's
achievements to Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics as well as to a series of correct policies
formulated by the veteran statesman.
</P>
<P>
He concluded the interview with full conviction that the
policies to be worked out at the upcoming congress of the Chinese
Communist Party scheduled for September 12 will further push
forward China's reforms and promote its economy.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that China will become a strong socialist country in
the near future and contribute more to the stability and
development of the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
