<HEADLINE> Philippine Tourist Arrivals Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Philippine tourist arrivals
hit 1,038,356 in the first six months of this year, an 11.17
percent hike from some 940,000 visitors registered in the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Department of Tourism today show that
Americans topped the foreign visitor arrivals, accounting for
23.12 percent of the total for the semester.
</P>
<P>
The department said it expected tourist arrivals this year to
top the two million mark since there are generally more visitors
in the second half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The nation's tourism industry has taken center stage with the
declared observance of National Tourism Month this September, with
all 13 tourism regional offices of the country taking active
promotional drives to push the gains of the industry.
</P>
<P>
One special highlight of the observance will be the Chefs on
Parade program on September 26-28 to be held in Manila.  
</P>
