<HEADLINE> Passenger Car Sales Decline in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Passenger car sales for the
first eight months of the year in the Philippines declined to
55,484 units from last year's 58,391 units.
</P>
<P>
Data released today by the Chamber of Automotive Manufacturers
of the Philippines show car sales for August also declined by 9
percent to 6,799 units from 7,478 units.
</P>
<P>
Honda Cars Philippines Inc. led sales for the month as it sold
1,755 units or 26 percent of the market.
</P>
<P>
This was followed by Mitsubishi Motors Phils. with 1,526 units;
Toyota Motor Phils. Corporation with 1,417 units and Nissan Motor
Phils. Inc. with 1,162 units.  
