<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Stephen Mak, Assistant Chief
Director of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council, said recently
that he thought the forthcoming 15th CPC National Congress would
draw up a development plan for the next century.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Mak, who has worked in Beijing for many years and is
quite familiar with the interior, said the majority of people
in Hong Kong knew that interior China and Hong Kong had achieved
rapid development in the past 18 years, mainly due to the reform
and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
The people have benefited from the policy formulated at the
Third Plenary Session of the 11th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1978, and are interested in the
15th CPC National Congress after Hong Kong has returned to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese people had accepted the idea of the
socialist market economy and achieved great successes in economic
development in the past five years, thus laying a solid
foundation for drafting development plans for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"I think that whatever the strategy is, the state
policy of reform and opening-up of China will not be changed," he
said. "This is the common wish of the whole Chinese people
including those in Hong Kong."
</P>
