<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, South Korea Sign Soft Loan Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and the
Export-Import Bank of Korea, the official Korean agency of
Economic Development Cooperation Fund, have signed a soft loan
agreement here Tuesday, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Bangladesh will get a loan worth 33.00
million U.S. dollars for purchasing 19 diesel-electric locomotives
for Bangladesh railway.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is becoming one of the important bilateral
development partners of Bangladesh both in public and private
sector, the sources said, adding that it has already provided a
loan of 14.00 million dollars which is being used for
implementation of a power project.
</P>
<P>
Besides this, it provided about four million dollars as grant
under which a hospital is being constructed. It also provided
training facilities to Bangladesh for human resources development,
the sources stated.  
</P>
