<HEADLINE> China Pacific Insurance Relocates to the Bund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Pacific Insurance
Company, the nation's first commercial shareholding insurer,
announced today that it has moved its headquarters to the
Bond, the most famous financial street in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Pacific become the first Chinese financial institution to move
to the Bund which is lined with numerous office buildings
belonging to overseas multinationals, according to Pacific General
Manager Li Xueqian.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the company, which was founded in Shanghai six
years ago, has set up a nationwide network of 58 branch companies
and nearly 300 offices. The company has also established
subsidiaries in Hong Kong and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Pacific reported a sharp increase in premium income in the
first half of this year, with a dramatic 44 percent period
increase to 6.74 billion yuan (812 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company's total premium income for 1996 approached 10
billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars).  
