<HEADLINE> Taiwan-Backed Motorcycle Production In Southeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A Taiwan-backed motorcycle
company in the city of Xiamen in east China's Fujian province has
set a goal of 500,000 motorcycles annually in the next five years,
making it one of the country's ten largest motorcycle producers.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaxing Motorcycle Co. Ltd. was funded by the Chingfong
Group, the largest motorcycle maker in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture has completed its first-phase construction on
a 45-million-US-dollar factory with an annual production capacity
of 120,000 motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
Xiaxing plans to spend 15 million US dollars on increasing
annual motorcycle engine output to 200,000 from the current
120,000. It also intends to have an annual production capacity of
one million motors within the next five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
