<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng To Speak At World Bank Hong Kong Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng will attend
the opening ceremony of the World Bank (WB) and International
Monetary Fund (IMF) annual meetings in Hong Kong later this month,
Xinhua has learned today.
</P>
<P>
As head of government of the host country, Li is expected to
speak at the opening ceremony of the meetings, scheduled from
September 23 to 25, the State Council Information Office says.
</P>
<P>
These are the first high-level international events in Hong
Kong since China resumed the exercise of sovereignty on July
1.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government delegation will consist of senior
officials from the Finance Ministry, the People's Bank of China,
the State Planning Commission, and other ministries. The
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region will
have its own delegates in the Chinese delegation.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) is handling
preparations for the meetings, which will be attended by finance
ministers and central bank governors from about 180 WB and IMF
member countries, heads of state of a number of countries, more
than 4,000 bankers and entrepreneurs, and over 2,000 reporters.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to discuss a wide range of global economic
and financial issues, internal affairs at the WB and IMF,
controlling finance market risk, and reducing the debt of
some developing countries. The total number of participants is expected to
exceed 20,000, more than at any previous annual meetings.
</P>
