<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Telecom To Introduce Asia's 1st Name Display Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Over 170,000 Hongkong
Telecom Caller Display service subscribers will be able to see the
name of the caller before answering a call starting mid-October
when the company launches Asia's first Name Display service.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom, a leading telecom services provider, was
recently given the go ahead to launch the new feature of the
Caller Display service. The Name Display feature will allow both
the caller and the called party to more efficiently manage their
communication.
</P>
<P>
An independent market research conducted in June on the Caller
Display service showed that the majority of the over 1,000
business and residential users interviewed found the service
useful and convenient to use. Over 95 percent of the interviewees
said they knew about the line blocking function, yet over 70
percent never thought of using it.
</P>
<P>
This finding matched customer response gauged in mid-1995
before the service was launched. Seventy percent of the
respondents indicated then that they did not mind releasing their
numbers to the called parties.
</P>
<P>
Interviewees also said the service is an effective device for
screening calls and logging unattended calls.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether Name Display would be a useful enhancement
to the service, 80 percent of the interviewees said "yes". This
positive customer response is what prompted the company to
introduce the new feature.
</P>
<P>
Prudence Chan, director of Hongkong Telecom, said: "The new
Name Display feature is just like an electronic business card. It
enables the caller to introduce or identify himself or his company
to the called party even before the call is answered. For the
called party, the function helps him know who exactly is calling
and therefore enables him to prepare to answer the call."
</P>
</TEXT>
