<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Hosts Biggest Watch, Clock Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A watch and clock fair, the
world's largest in terms of number of exhibitors, opened today in
Hong Kong, known as the center for mass production of medium and
lower-end watches.
</P>
<P>
About 770 timepiece manufacturers from 17 countries and regions
displayed their latest designs in an exhibition area of more than
25,000 square meters at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
Despite pressing market challenges, Hong Kong's watch and clock
industry remains in excellent shape, said Donald Tsang, Financial
Secretary of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) at
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the world's second largest exporter of watches,
both in value and in quantity; It is the world's top exporter of
clocks in value and comes to the second in quantity. Besides, the
watch and clock industry is the third manufacturing sector in the
city.
</P>
<P>
To ensure competitive pricing by lowering production costs,
Hong Kong watch manufacturers have shifted their workshops to
areas where labor and land costs are lower, notably inland areas
of China and Southeast Asia, according to the official. Hong Kong
has turned out to be a strategic center, focusing on product
design, quality control, marketing and trade.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is a leading trader of watches, clocks and timepiece
components. It exported nearly 48 billion HK dollars (6.1 billion
US dollars) worth of such products in 1996, mainly to the United
States, the Chinese inland areas, Japan, Germany, the United
Kingdom and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Hong Kong imported almost 40 billion HK dollars (5.1
billion US dollars) worth of timepieces, with the Chinese inland
areas, Japan, Switzerland, Thailand, Singapore and Taiwan as the
leading supplier.
</P>
<P>
Anthony Wong, co-chairman of the fair said today Hong Kong, as
an important market and trading hub of timepieces in Asia, has
become an ideal location for the fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
