secretary of Australia's Department of Defense, said China
attaches importance to its friendly relations with Australia and
hopes that the development trend between the two countries and
their armed forces will be maintained.
</P>
<P>
Ayers said the Australian government will continue to pursue
its "one China" policy and will not have any official relations
with Taiwan, and said he hopes that China's peaceful reunification
will go smoothly because it will benefit China, the region, and
the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also state councillor, said the Taiwan issue is an
internal affair that can be settled if foreign countries do not
interfere and he expressed his appreciation for the Australian
government's "one China" stand.
</P>
<P>
The "one country, two systems" and "peaceful reunification"
policies initiated by Deng Xiaoping remain China's policy for
Taiwan, he noted. The smooth return of Hong Kong proved that the
"one country, two systems" policy is correct, and China is fully
confident in national reunification.
</P>
<P>
Chi briefed his guest on China's foreign policy of peace and
its national defense and noted that building up China's defense
forces will serve its central task of economic construction.
</P>
<P>
