<HEADLINE> Reception for Journalists Covering 15th Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A reception was held here
today for Chinese and overseas journalists who have come to cover
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
which is scheduled to open on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 500 Chinese and overseas journalists attended the
reception in the Great Hall of the People, hosted by the Press
Center of the congress.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, the two spokesmen for the congress -- Xu
Guangchun, deputy head of the Propaganda Department of the CPC
Central Committee, and Li Bing, deputy director of the Information
Office of the State Council, and other leading members of the
press group of the congress -- were introduced to the journalists.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zheren, director of the Press Center of the congress, said
that the convening of the 15th National Congress of the CPC has
attracted both Chinese and overseas wide attention.
</P>
<P>
By noon today, a total of 1,043 journalists had registered to
cover the congress, a notable increase over the number of those
who covered the 14th CPC National Congress in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Among the journalists, 156 came from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, 72 from Taiwan and Macao regions, and 410
from foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
The Press Center, based in the Media Hotel, will help arrange
reporters to cover the opening session of the congress, and help
arrange press briefings, press conferences and collective
interviews. Panel discussions of some delegations will also be
open to the press during the congress. The center will also help
contact some delegates for press interviews, and it will also
provide the reporters with background information and telecom
service.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that so many Chinese and overseas journalists have
come to cover the forthcoming 15th CPC National Congress shows
that the congress not only is of great historical significance to
the development of our country and the Chinese nation, but also
has a vital bearing on world peace and development," a leading
official of the Press Center said, adding that the event has drawn
the close attention of the world media.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials of the Press Center also answered some
questions raised by the journalists present.  
</P>
</TEXT>
