<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Hungarian Military Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Chi Haotian, Chinese defense
minister and vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, met
here today with Lieutenant General Vegh Ferenc, commander and
chief of the general staff of the National Army of Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a state councillor, said that China and Hungary are
free of any conflicts of interest, share common interests and have
recorded sound development in various areas.
</P>
<P>
According to Chi, friendly cooperation between the two
countries and their armed forces should continue to grow in spite
of changes in the worldwide situation. He noted that the view
represents the consensus of both state leaders and military heads
of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Hungary are important nations in Asia and Europe, and
both are engaged in efforts to safeguard world peace and promote
national economic development, said Chi, adding that the two
countries should support and assist each other.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the convinction that Vegh's current visit will
undoubtedly promote the existing bilateral military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Vegh noted long-lasting good relationship between Hungary and
China. He said that China plays an important role in maintaining
regional and world peace and security, and said that Hungary hopes
to expand friendly cooperation between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Vegh said he is delighted to see the further development in
friendly cooperation between the two armed forces and expressed
belief that his current China trip will be highly significant in
promoting bilateral military contacts.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Hungary will maintain its "one China"
policy, and said that the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate representative for China. 
</P>
