<HEADLINE> NATO-Russia Council Ministers to Meet in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The first ministerial
meeting of the NATO-Russia Joint Council will be held later this
month to discuss the development in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The council meeting, scheduled for September 26 in New York, is
also expected to ratify a work schedule of dismantlement policy
for Russia's nuclear weapons, nuclear safety and the beginning of
military-to-military cooperation between Russia and the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), a NATO press release said
today.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting will be jointly chaired by NATO chief
Javier Solana, Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov and
Belgian Foreign Minister Erik Derycke who is now serving as the
chairman of the NATO Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
