<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress Attracts 1000-plus Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua)-- A total of 1,043 Chinese and
foreign journalists have applied to cover the forthcoming CPC 15th
National Congress by noon today, nearly twice the number of those
who covered the 14th National Party Congress, official sources here
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the press center of the congress, the coming CPC
meeting has attracted such worldwide attention that the center has
kept receiving applications even after the official deadline on
September 8.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,000-plus reporters registered with the center, 156 are
from 28 press organizations of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, six from four Macao press organizations and
66 from 22 Taiwan press organizations. More than 130 press
organizations in 50 countries have sent 410 reporters to cover the
event.
</P>
<P>
A leading official of the press center said that the fact that
so many Chinese and foreign journalists have come to cover the
congress shows that the coming CPC national congress not only is
of great historic significance to China and the Chinese nation,
but also has a vital bearing on world peace and development. The
press center will try its best to provide conveniences for their
coverage, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
