<HEADLINE> Lithuania Praises Close Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VILNIUS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania is proud of and
sincerely values the close economic relations with China,
Lithuanian Foreign Minister Algirdas Suadargas said today in an
exclusive interview with Xinhua news agency.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania congratulates China on the successful economic
reform, which has guaranteed the country a position among the
major economic powers in the world, Suadargas said.
</P>
<P>
"Since 1978, starting with the 'opening up policy' initiated by
Deng Xiaoping," the minister said, "China's economic system has
changed dramatically and this can be expressed by the significant
achievements in all fields of national economy."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese reform strategy "to embark on
far-reaching economic liberalization and to integrate China into
the world economy is bearing fruits and could serve as a good
example for many developing countries."
</P>
<P>
On the bilateral relations, Suadargas pointed out Lithuania
recognized the government of the People's Republic of China as the
sole legitimate government of China. This principle constitutes
the basis for good relations between the two countries at present
and for the years to come.
</P>
<P>
Suadargas said that in recent years numerous high level visits
between the two countries resulted in eight state agreements,
which had founded firm legal basis for the economic cooperation.
</P>
