<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Helps Poor Escape Poverty This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province will try to get its remaining 560,000 poor people out of
poverty by the end of this year, according to Vice-governor Xu
Wencai.
</P>
<P>
The province had 16 poor counties with 3.6 million people
living below the poverty line a decade ago, but they are down to
five counties now.
</P>
<P>
The central and provincial governments have offered more than
700 million yuan in loans to help the poor areas develop, and
these relief funds have added 1.3 billion yuan in output value,
benefitting 900,000 households.
</P>
<P>
The state also gave nearly 500 million yuan in a
relief-through-work program and the province allocated 100 million
yuan for drinking water for 1.2 million people and 250,000 head of
livestock.
</P>
<P>
Jianping County has developed eight regional industries,
increasing agricultural and industrial production 5-fold, township
enterprise output 10-fold, and revenues more than 20-fold.
</P>
<P>
Chaoyang city, over the past 10 years, improved some 700,000 ha
of barren land and dredged 2,200 km of waterways, bringing
three-quarters of the area plagued by soil erosion under control,
and doubling the local grain output.
</P>
<P>
The province has paid great attention to science and
technology, promoting more than 200 scientists to deputy county
magistrates or putting them in charge of science and technology
work in most township governments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
