<HEADLINE> Port Network Promoting Foreign Trade in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A complete port network has
greatly enhanced the development of foreign trade in east China's
Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
There are nine Category-A and Category-B ports of entry in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's ports has handled more than 2.7 million tons of foreign
trade materials between 1993 and June this year, with annual
average growth standing at 47.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province's airports handled 110,000 passengers during the
period.  
</P>
