<HEADLINE> Angola, S. Africa to Promote Heath Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Health Minister
Anastacio Sicato said here on Tuesday night that his country will
strengthen its ties with South Africa in the field of health.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement to the press after attending a west
African regional meeting of the World Heath Organization (WHO)
held in South Africa and talks with his South African
counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will hold a joint technical meeting next
February to discuss concrete issues concerning bilateral health
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, reports reaching here said Tokvo Sexwale, governor
of Gauteng Province in South Africa, expressed his worries during
his visit to Luanda on Monday that many patients in the hospitals
are not receiving timely treatment and rescue, and wished that they
would be transferred to South Africa for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The medical circles of the two countries will coordinate work
in this regard. Moreover, South Africa will send doctors to work
in hospitals in Luanda.
</P>
<P>
Sicato believed that this is only one facet of bilateral
cooperation in health, saying the two sides will broaden the
areas for cooperation to promote health development in Angola.
</P>
</TEXT>
