<HEADLINE> Book Fair Witnesses Increasing Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A national book fair, which
ended last week in Changchun, set a record with orders valued at
509 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The over 5,000 publishers from across the country attending the
fair offered 210,000 publications titles, the majority of which
have been published over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 transactions were recorded for 1,200-odd copyrights on
offer during the fair.
</P>
<P>
Organizers noted the fact that publications for children and
grade school students were the most popular items in terms of
order volume, which indicates that most readers purchase books to
supplement educational activities.
</P>
<P>
The number of history books and biographies published in recent
years has increased in recent years, while the number of novels
published has been on the decline. 
</P>
