<HEADLINE> Kenya to Host Regional Investment Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A regional investment
promotion conference is scheduled to be held in Nairobi in
November this year, the "Kenya Times" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper quoted the Executive Director of the
Investments Promotion Center Joseph Ng'ok as saying Tuesday that
the two-day conference was aimed at discussing, among other
things, inter-regional investments and cross border trade.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that with the revival of the East African
Co-operation (EAC), cross border trade within the region had
drastically increased and urged for an improved government-level
interaction.
</P>
<P>
"The only way forward to cement this cross border trade is a
frequent interaction at the government level to give it moral
support," he added.
</P>
<P>
Ng'ok noted that this is the first meeting of the EAC
investments promotion bodies which would be held annually in the
future.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will bring together the Kenya Investments
Promotion Center, the Uganda Investment Promotion Authority and
the Tanzania Investments Promotion Agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
