<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen, Hong Kong Waterway Project Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning
Commission recently gave the nod of approval for the building of
the Tonggu Waterway between Shenzhen and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Local officials call it an important step to link transport
facilities between Shenzhen and neighboring Hong Kong. The Tonggu
project is the first such work okayed by the central government
this year.
</P>
<P>
The work is primarily a deep-water exiting channel for the
western part of the Shenzhen Harbor. In the first phase, the
waterway will be able to accomodate new type of container-carriers.
</P>
<P>
The new waterway will be 200 meters in width at its bottom and
13.5 meters in depth. Total cost of the work is estimated to reach
about 680 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
There are now 85 berths in western port area, handling a total
of 27.5 million tons of goods last year, including 236,000 TEUs.
</P>
<P>
However, up to now, all huge vessels have had to enter the port
through Hong Kong's waterway, which is unsafe due to its speedy
water-flow and a number of submerged reefs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
