<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wuhan Agriculture Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Wuhan's agriculture sector,
which features ideal natural and geographical conditions, has
emerged as a preferred investment choice for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Chinese urbanites are gradually abandoning the habit of buying
live chickens, and are instead opting for Chai Tai packaged
chicken cooperatively produced by the city and the Chai Tai Group
from Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the group invested 194 million US dollars to construct
the largest chicken processing enterprise in central China's Wuhan
City.
</P>
<P>
The company provides hatchlings and feed, and teaches farmers
epidemic prevention techniques. The farmers then supply the
company with mature chickens.
</P>
<P>
The group's annual processing capacity stands at three million
packaged chickens which are sold at home and overseas.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors had opened 15 agriculture-related
enterprises valued at 500 million US dollars in the city by the
end of August. The enterprises are engaged in wide-ranging areas
such as aquatic products, flower cultivation, cultivation,
beverages, and livestock products processing.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Israel established Asia's largest dehydrated
vegetable processing enterprise in Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
The city, located at the juncture of east and west China,
features convenient water, land and air transportation. Some 255
frost-free days annually provide ideal conditions for farming,
especially for growing vegetables and fruit.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan's 118,000 ha of water coverage also offer great potential
for the development of aquatic products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moon Cakes Fulfill Quality Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey revealed that
most packaged moon cakes fulfill quality standards expected by
shoppers purchasing the festive food for the coming Mid-Autumn
Festival.
</P>
<P>
The traditional Mid-Autumn Festival falls on September 16 this
year, or the 15th of August according to the Lunar
Calendar. Families across the nation traditionally gather to enjoy
moon cakes on the day which is similar to western celebrations
such as Thanksgiving.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey by the Ministry of Internal Trade revealed that
90.2 percent of packaged moon cakes sold this year fulfill quality
criterion, compared to only 57.7 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The survey, which was carried out by four ministry's quality
examination centers, examined 102 varieties of moon cakes
producted by 93 factories in cities, including Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou, Tianjin, Hangzhou, Suzhou and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Items were inspected for hygiene standards, weight, content and
labels.
</P>
<P>
Four producers of seven varieties of substandard moon cakes
were named in a ministry's press conference on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
