<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rising Shanghai Industrial Production-Sales Ratio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Marketing efforts carried
out by Shanghai entrepreneurs yielded an industrial
production-sales ratio of 96.6 percent in the first half of this
year, up 0.59 percentage points on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that rising production-sales ratios were
recorded for 76 of 129 major industrial products, with exceptional
sales for electrical appliances and electronic products.
</P>
<P>
The production-sales ratio for refrigerators topped 176
percent, up 81 percentage points on the 1996 period. The city's
enterprises sold out all the program-controlled switches, fax
machines, color kinescopes and hi-fi systems they produced during
the period.
</P>
<P>
Strengthened promotions and controlled production enabled
Shanghai's textile to record a production-sales ratio of 100.4
percent in the first half of the year, with the percentage of
stockpiled garments dropping by 13 points.
</P>
<P>
The production-sales ratio for fuel and fertilizer also fell
during the period.
</P>
<P>
The overall sales value of the city's industrial enterprises
totaled 259.9 billion yuan in the first half of 1997, up 12.8
percent on the 1996 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
