<HEADLINE> Jinan Banking Sector Grows Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The financial sector in Jinan,
capital of east China's Shandong Province, has experienced rapid
growth in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 1,400 financial institutions in
Jinan employ over 18,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The city banking system reported total deposits of 59.5 billion
yuan (7.2 billion US dollars) by the end of June, a four-fold
increase on the total at the 1991. In addition, the loans volume
of 47 billion yuan represented a three-fold rise on 1991.
</P>
<P>
Jinan has withdrawn a total of more than 10 billion yuan from
circulation since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Jinan's foreign exchange deposits stand at over 300 million US
dollars, with the city's annual insurance premiums standing at 600
million yuan. 
