<HEADLINE> Picture Album Published to Show Deng Xiaoping's Merits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- China's first large photo
album illustrating Deng Xiaoping's theory and practice of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics has been recently published
by the Liaoning Ethnic Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The "Cross-century Historical Picture Album", with more than
600 pictures and 130,000 Chinese characters, describes the forming
and the main content of Deng's theory on building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
It also shows the great achievements China has scored in the
reform, opening up and socialist modernization drive over the past
two decades and reflects the country's bright future.
</P>
<P>
The album consists of 17 sections, covering Deng's basic
theory, basic lines and development strategy as well as the
country's rural reform, market economy, state-owned enterprises,
opening up, democracy and legal system, national unity, military
affairs and national defense, cultural and ethic progress as well
as foreign affairs and Party building. 
</P>
