<HEADLINE> Fujian-Hong Kong Economic Cooperation Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Fujian-Hongkong Economic
Cooperation Promotion Committee has been formed to further expand
economic cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Fujian Governor He Guoqiang serves as the director of the
committee, which was set up on Monday, with 41 of 68 members
coming from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, the province's largest trade partner, is a major
source of investment and tourism, as well as an important link in
economic relations between Fujian and Taiwan, according to the
governor.
</P>
<P>
The committee will focus on investigations and research related
to cooperative opportunities in the fields of finance, investment,
trade and other important sectors. It will also be responsible for
adopting overall arrangements and policies to guide related
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The committee is expected to play a major role in convincing
Hong Kong entrepreneurs to invest in the province and will serve
as a link to lure the multinational corporations and financial
groups, He said. 
