<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Economic and
Technological Development Zone, located in the capital of
Guangdong Province, has recorded steady development by introducing
an increasing number of large and hi-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
Japan and a number of countries in Europe and the Americas have
contributed more than half overseas investment in the zone, with
the influx of investments from Hong Kong and Macao falling from 80
percent to 42 percent.
</P>
<P>
The zone has attracted funding from some 40 of the world's top
500 industrial enterprises and has emerged as a preferred
investment site for rising number of multinational companies, with
90 industrial projects involving investments of over 10 million US
dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The zone's investment focus has shifted from daily-use products
to a series of hi-tech products.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou zone has attempted to improve the product mix by
emphasizing hi-tech projects related to refined chemicals, health
care, raw materials for industrial use, automobile parts,
electronic components, iron and steel, food and beverages, and
packaging materials.  
</P>
