<HEADLINE> U.S. Open Badminton Grand Prix Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Following are results
Tuesday at the U.S. Open Badminton Grand Prix in Orange,
California (prefix number denotes seeding):
</P>
<P>
Men's singles, second round:
</P>
<P>
1-Dong Jiong, China, bt Howard Bach, United States, 15-7 15-3
</P>
<P>
2-Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen, Denmark, bt Patrice Ritchie, Canada,
15-2, 15-2
</P>
<P>
3-Peter Rasmussen, Denmark, bt Jon Frisch, United States,
15-4, 15-6
</P>
<P>
4-Ardy Wiranta, Indonesia, bt Mark Manha, United States, 15-5,
15-6
</P>
<P>
Alan Budi Kusuma, Indonesia, bt Martin Lundgaard, Denmark,
15-7, 15-1
</P>
<P>
Peter Gade Christensen, Denmark, bt Iain Sydie, Canada, by
default
</P>
<P>
Sun Ho Hwang, South Korea, bt Hidetaka Yamada, Japan, 15-4,
15-6
</P>
<P>
Jeroen van Dijk, Netherlands, bt Bruce Flockhart, Scotland,
15-10, 15-5
</P>
<P>
Hermawan Susanto, Indonesia, bt Jeng-Shuyuang Chang, Chinese
Taipei, 5-15, 15-11, 15-8
</P>
<P>
Tomas Johansson, Sweden, bt Andy Chong, United States, 15-7,
15-2
