<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou-Zhuhai Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The central government has
recently approved the construction of a railway linking Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, with Zhuhai City
which neighbors Macao.
</P>
<P>
The railway, one of the five major infrastructure projects for
Zhuhai, a special economic zone, is of great importance for
ensuring the city's sustained development, according to local
government officials.
</P>
<P>
The 142-km railway will be built at a cost of some 3.4 billion
yuan. First phase will involve laying a double-track foundation
and a single track. Future plans calls for the railway to be
an electrified quasi-high-speed railway.
</P>
<P>
The four other key infrastructure projects scheduled for
construction in the special economic zone are the Zhuhai Airport,
Zhuhai Port, the Zhuhai Power Plant, and the Coastal Expressway.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
