<HEADLINE> E. African Countries Urged to Harmonize Cultural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Harmonization of the
cultural and educational policies in Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda
has been urged for faster regional integration.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by the Deputy Executive Secretary of the
East African Cooperation (EAC), Fulgence Kazaura, in Arusha,
northern Tanzania Tuesday, while opening a three-day meeting of
senior officials of culture and education sector from the three
countries, according to a news dispatch available here today.
</P>
<P>
"The people of east Africa share common heritage in language
and traditional values," said Kazaura, adding "These are the
factors which can be utilized for the mutual benefit of the
member states within the framework of the EAC."
</P>
<P>
He noted that culture and education are crucial for promoting
fraternal relations and enhancing social integration of peoples
of the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
Kazaura asked the delegates to the meeting to identity
constraints that confront EAC member states in the area and make
recommendations which will be followed by relevant authorities.
</P>
