<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: Chinese Economic Development is a Miracle: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The reform and opening policy,
launched by the Communist Party of China in the late 1970s, has
brought miraculous economic development to the country, said Anwar
Hossain, who just returned from China last month.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, Hossain, general secretary
of the Bangladesh-China Friendship Center, said China has set an
example in the world of magnificent economic development while
keeping the social and moral values intact.
</P>
<P>
Noting that over the past 19 years, China's GDP has registered
an average annual growth of 9.9 percent, he said, "the economic
development taken place in China can only be compared with dreams
come true."
</P>
<P>
Anwarul Amin, who was a chief executive of an international
bank in Beijing in the 1980s, said in a separate interview with
Xinhua that he had witnessed the great development since 1978 when
the reform and opening policy came into effect.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his seven-year stay in Beijing, he said: "I saw
visibly the gradual evolution of the Chinese open policy and also
the Chinese emphasis on having market economy orientation along
with Socialist characteristics, which I think was a unique way of
thinking."
</P>
<P>
"When I had a chance to go again to China in this July, I was
really astonished by the speed of the progress during the last few
years," said Amin, who attributed all these achievements to the
correct policy taken by the Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Chairman Jainul Jamal of Diot Corporation, one of the leading
Bangladeshi importers of Chinese agricultural and industrial
machinery and electric motors, told Xinhua that his company's
yearly trade volume with China had gone up to 20 million U.S.
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
"For the considerable price and quality, Chinese products
exported to our country are acceptable in all quarters. In fact,
almost all Bangladesh workshops are using the exported machinery
goods of China," said Jamal.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, I took very often business trips to China and
I was deeply impressed by the unprecedented economic reform and
social development taken by the Chinese government. In my opinion,
the policy progress of China in every respect is encouraging," he
added.
</P>
<P>
As for the forthcoming 15th Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), Amin believed that the congress will come up with a
better and more progressive reform package following evaluation of
the experience in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
"With many young, energetic and dynamic people entering the
party leadership, the CPC is fully geared up to take the challenge
of the 21st century. I will say the party is on the right track
and the people are very happy seeing this reforms working in their
own life," he added.
</P>
<P>
Hossain is also confident of the new leadership in China,
"President Jiang Zemin is already leading the country toward right
direction. The successful reunification of Hong Kong has
manifested the achievement of new leaders."
</P>
<P>
"We hope the Chinese new leadership will be able to face any
challenge in achieving economic and social development in the
coming days," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
