<HEADLINE> Lebanon and Romania to Enhance Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon wishes to strengthen
its economic and trade ties with Romania, Lebanese Parliament
President Nabih Berri told a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Berri, who is now on a four-day official visit to Romania, held
talks with Romanian Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea, Chairman of the
Senate Petre Roman and Chairman of the Chamber of Deputies Jan
Diaconescu.
</P>
