During their talks, the two sides mainly discussed ways to
enhance bilateral trade ties. Berri pointed out that so far the
two countries have signed nine agreements on cooperation in trade,
tourism and other fields. However, there was great potential for
further cooperation in bilateral trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on the Middle East peace
process. Berri expressed appreciation for Romania's support for
Lebanon in upholding its independence. He hoped that Romania would
play a greater role in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Berri arrived here on Sunday and was scheduled to wind up his
visit tomorrow. 
