<HEADLINE> Oil Prices Keep Rising in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Motor fuel prices in Thailand
are still on the rise as a result of the Thai currency's
floatation since July 2.
</P>
<P>
Service stations operated by the two major
government-controlled oil firms raised oil prices across the board
on Tuesday by 30 satang a liter, the 10th round of oil price
hikes since the baht's floatation.
</P>
<P>
Up until now the value of the baht has depreciated about 40
percent against the U.S. dollar, which is used by the country in
the import of oil.
</P>
<P>
Oil prices have gone up about once a week since mid-July, each
time by a margin of between 20-30 satang.
</P>
<P>
The accumulated increase in domestic oil prices since July 16,
when oil companies first began to boost pump prices, is in the
range of 1.6-1.7 baht a liter.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's price hike by the two government-controlled oil
firms, Petroleum Authority of Thailand and Bangchuk Petroleum Plc,
followed decisions last Saturday by the other major oil companies
to raise prices by the same margin.
</P>
<P>
A liter of super gasoline now costs about 11.3 baht while
premium gasoline is about 11.2 baht a liter.
</P>
<P>
Domestic pump prices are now the highest over the past several
years.
</P>
<P>
Given the volatile situation, local pump prices will likely
jump again by the same amount on Saturday as major firms seek to
cover the actual increase in their costs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970910.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Push Floriculture Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has decided to
develop its floriculture industry and make it competitive in the
world market.
</P>
<P>
A six-member committee has been appointed by the government to
study all aspects of the industry and make recommendations.
</P>
<P>
At present only a few Sri Lankan companies are exporting a
small quantity of cut flowers, ornamental plants and foliage
plants to the European Union and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The government believes that if the industry is well organized
and coordinated, it could compete with India, Thailand and
Malaysia for a larger market share.
</P>
<P>
Floriculture is a booming industry in India, Thailand and
Malaysia, where it often gets support and assistance from the
government.
</P>
<P>
The committee will carry out a survey to evaluate the current
situation of the industry, such as the number of projects in
operation, extent of land cultivation, annual production and
volume of exports.
</P>
<P>
It will also make recommendations on the development of the
floriculture industry and the extent of state assistance to such
development efforts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
