<HEADLINE> Overseas Funds for South China's Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of
China's Guangdong Province, has used more than 286 million US
dollars in overseas funds for 170 overseas-fund rural agriculture
projects, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Investors from Hong Kong, Taiwan and Japan are involved in
vegetable, fruit, and flower production and seed growing, as well
as farm product-processing and village-based tourism.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou is a fast developing metropolis that is trying to
improve investment environment for farming.
</P>
<P>
The local government has spent one billion yuan (120.5 million
US dollars) annually on irrigation works for the past few years,
and farmland with stable yields accounts for 83.5 percent of the
total amount of land.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech agro-industries have contributed a lot to the rapid
development, and the city has restructured the agricultural sector
to turn it into "high-quality, high-output and high-efficiency"
operation.
</P>
<P>
The local government has also built wholesale markets for farm
products.  
</P>
