<HEADLINE> Czech Republic Seeks EC Flood Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic applied on
Monday to the European Commission (EC) for economic aid to help
its flood-hit areas recover from the natural disaster which
occurred early July.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of money the Czech Republic applied for is
38.4 million ECU (53.8 million U.S. dollars), of which 28.3
million ECU (39.7 million dollars) would be used to rebuild
infrastructure in flooded areas, and the rest would aid small and
medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The floods, triggered by continuous torrential rains in the
eastern part of the Czech Republic, led to 46 deaths and massive
property damage.
</P>
<P>
The Czech government has adopted a series of measures to help
the flood-hit areas resume production and rebuild homes.
</P>
<P>
The EC granted 65 million ECU to Poland in late July for the
same humanitarian purposes. 
</P>
