<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Train Higher Clinical Science Specialists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is conducting the
first higher specialist training program to produce more qualified
higher grade professionals and the trainees will be conferred the
doctorate in medical science.
</P>
<P>
The training program, which was opened here Tuesday, is aimed
at providing higher post-graduate training, producing highly
qualified doctors, upgrading the level of clinical competency and
keeping abreast with the international level, the official paper
The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The program covers assessment of the performance of the
candidates by a panel of local and foreign experts and juries.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's medical education has been offering up to master's
degree courses since 1907.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 17 master's degree courses and five diploma courses
have been conducted, producing 1,338 master's degree holders and
858 diploma holders, the report added.  
