<HEADLINE> Argentina Posts Trade Deficit in First Seven Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Argentina registered a
1.86 billion dollar trade deficit during the first seven months of
this year, said the National Institute of Statistics and Census
today.
</P>
<P>
Imports jumped 28 percent over the corresponding previous
period to 16.59 billion dollars, while exports rose only 9 percent
to reach 14.73 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, the country posted a 1.2 billion dollar trade surplus
with its partners in the Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the biggest trade bloc in South America, groups
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, with Bolivia and Chile
being associate members. 
</P>
