<HEADLINE> Albanian Leader Stresses Cooperation With European Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Albanian Prime
Minister Fatos Nano said here today that his government is
launching a "new diplomatic offensive" which will focus on
promoting cooperation between Albania and European organizations.
</P>
<P>
Nano, who arrived here earlier today on a visit to Austria and
the Vienna-based Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE), told a press conference that the new coalition
government of Albania will work closely with the OSCE and the
European Union to guarantee human rights and civil freedoms in the
chaos-torn country.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government will also cooperate with the European
bodies to ensure that power can no longer be abused in this Balkan
nation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Later, Nano conferred Albania's highest honor, the Skanderbeg
award, on former Austrian chancellor Franz Vranitzky who acted as
the OSCE special envoy to Albania and made great contributions to
the restoration of peace in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albania began sinking into chaos earlier this year, which was
triggered by the collapse of pyramid investment schemes in which
hundreds of thousands people lost money.
</P>
<P>
Nano became new prime minister of a five-party coalition
government at the end of June in a general election organized in
large part by the OSCE.
</P>
<P>
Nano held talks with Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schuessel later in the day but no details are available so far.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian prime minister will meet Austrian National Council
President Heinz Fischer on Wednesday before leaving for Brussels
to continue his European tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
