<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo fired the chief of his Institutional Revolutionary Party
(PRI) today, two months after the party lost its absolute majority
in the Chamber of Deputies in mid-term elections.
</P>
