<HEADLINE> Under-17 Soccer Worlds Preliminary a Great Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Statistics released by the
Organizing Committee of the 4th Under-17 FIFA World Cup showed
that 16 matches, played until now, yielded a total of 55 goals,
amounting to an average of 3.44 goals per tie.
</P>
<P>
The U-17 championship, being held in four Egyptian cities on
September 4-21, recessed today before entering the last round of
group matches on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An unprecedented 80 teams fought for a slot into the 16 teams
now competing in four groups of the championship, which was
originated in Beijing in 1985 under the title of U-16 and changed
to U-17 in Italy in 1991. It was the first time for Egypt to host
a World Cup event.
</P>
<P>
Oman's striker Mohammad Saleh leads until now as the
competition's top scorer with 4 goals to his credit.
</P>
<P>
Brazil-Austria clash boasts the highest score of 7-0, and 14
matches ended with win, the statistics noted.
</P>
<P>
Only four send-offs were registered but the number of booked
players hit the 53 peak.
</P>
<P>
The number of spectators, who witnessed the 16 encounters,
amounted to 453,500, according to the statistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
