<HEADLINE> Canadian Sprinter Banned for Four Years for Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A young Canadian sprinter has
been banned for four years for testing positive for steroids, the
Athletics Canada announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Derek Dueck, who finished sixth in the 100
meters at the Canada Summer Games last month, was tested positive
for testosterone and epitestosterone, the Canadian national
governing body of track and field said.
</P>
<P>
But Dueck said he didn't take any banned substances and would
appeal to the decision.
</P>
<P>
Dueck argued that the abnormal levels of testosterone were "due
to a (legal) drug I was taking for medical purposes".
</P>
<P>
Dueck said he and his specialist consulted the banned substance
list before a prescription was written. 
</P>
