<HEADLINE> Mayor of Brazzaville Nominated as Congo's PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Congolese President Pascal
Lissouba has named Bernard Kolelas, mayor of the capital of
Brazzaville, as prime minister of a national unity government,
according to Radio Cameroun today.
</P>
<P>
In a broadcast on official radio in Congo, Lissouba said Mayor
Kolelas was nominated to the premiership on Moday.
</P>
<P>
As chairman of the National Mediation Committee, Mayor Kolelas
has since three months ago continued his efforts to end the civil
war between forces loyal to Lissouba and militia of former
president Sassou.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gabonese President Omar Bongo who is also chairman
of the International Mediation Committee of the Congolese
Conflict has put up several peaceful plans. The proposal to form
a national unity government in Congo is among these plans.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the post of the prime minister of the
national unity government should be resumed by the rival force.
</P>
<P>
Kolelas' nomination was strongly criticized by the forces of
Sassou. 
</P>
